  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are front hooks or back hooks more common in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Back hooks are significantly more common. Approximately 65-70% of Scrabble-valid words accept a back hook (most commonly S, D, or R), while only about 25% accept a front hook. This is because English word formation relies heavily on suffixes rather than single-letter prefixes." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the difference between a front hook and a back hook?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A front hook adds a letter to the beginning of an existing word (B+LOCK=BLOCK), while a back hook adds a letter to the end (LOCK+S=LOCKS). Both create new valid words from existing board words. Front hooks are less expected by opponents, making them powerful surprise plays." }
      },
